# Engineering Craft

- Write clear PR descriptions, RFCs, and incident notes so others can act without a meeting.
- Debug with hypotheses: isolate one variable, reproduce minimally, read source before guessing.
- Ship the right-sized solution; defer perfection when the 80% path unblocks the team.
- Give code review feedback that is specific, actionable, and tied to risk or maintainability.
- Stay curious at seniority: read upstream code, ask why systems behave as they do, update mental models.
